1) Explain about Selenium Architecture
Selenium is a architecture designed to facilitate automated interaction with web browsers. 
Working Flow:
  Selenium library --> w3c protocol --> Browser driver --> real browser(using http).

2)Write a program to open website (https://www.saucedemo.com/) and close the browser after priniting a message like "Site navigation success"
package practiceselenium;

import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.chrome.ChromeDriver;

public class seldayone {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		// TODO Auto-generated method stub
		WebDriver driver = new ChromeDriver();
		driver.get("https://www.saucedemo.com");
		System.out.println("Site navigation success");
		driver.close();
	}
}

